<p>The Church traditionally dedicates <strong>May</strong> to the <strong>Blessed Virgin Mary</strong>. The brotherhood uses this month to honour its Marian Titular, <strong>Our Lady Health of the Sick and Fountain of Salvation</strong>, in line with the Statutes (cf. Art. 1). May devotion complements—not replaces—other statutory celebrations.</p>
<h2>Parish and street</h2>
<p>With the spiritual director and parish priest, the worship commission may organise Marian Mass, public Rosary, modest floral offerings and catechesis. Events that include a route outside the church are grouped under <strong>external worship</strong> on this site. Times and venues are published in official channels.</p>
